  "selected_design_rationale": "The dominant design is the Fig. 1 / Table 1 proposed microstrip patch antenna: the paper frames it as the main antenna, gives its dimensions in the dedicated proposed-antenna table, and concludes with performance numbers for that antenna. The later beam-shaping section explicitly adds multiple copies into an antenna array for 3-sectorization, so it is treated as an extension, not the canonical single antenna. The feed is best interpreted as an inset-fed microstrip line, with the inset-feed schematic and text more specific than the broader generic 'microstrip line feeding' phrasing.",
  "selected_design_summary": "Single proposed rectangular microstrip patch antenna for 28 GHz 5G operation, using an inset-fed microstrip line, copper patch/ground, and a Rogers RT5880(lossy) substrate. Table 1 gives the main geometry, and the later beam-shaping discussion is a secondary array extension rather than the dominant antenna geometry.",
